兩種方式 Subplot 與 axes 皆有使用

In [1]:
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from keras.models import load_model
from keras.datasets import mnist
from keras.models import Sequential
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline

seed = 7
np.random.seed(seed)
(X_train, Y_train), (X_test, Y_test) = mnist.load_data()
model = Sequential()
model = load_model("./data/mnist.h5")
model.compile(loss = "categorical_crossentropy", optimizer = "adam", metrics = ["accuracy"])

Using TensorFlow backend.
In [2]:
listX = []
listY = []
for i in range(len(X_test)):
    digit = X_test[i].reshape(28,28)
    X_test_digit = X_test[i].reshape(1, 28, 28, 1).astype("float32")
    X_test_digit = X_test_digit/255
    probs = model.predict_proba(X_test_digit, batch_size = 1)
    if not probs[0][Y_test[i]] == probs.max():
        listX.append(i)
        listY.append(probs[0])

L = [0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75]
j = 0
count = 1
while j < 88:
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 100))
    plt.subplot(45, 4, count)
    plt.title("Example of Digit: "+ str(Y_test[listX[j]]))
    plt.imshow(X_test[listX[j]].reshape(28,28), cmap = "gray")
    plt.axis("off")
    count += 1

    probs = model.predict_proba(X_test_digit, batch_size = 1)
    plt.subplot(45, 4, count)
    plt.title("Probabilities for Each Digit Class")
    plt.bar(np.arange(10), listY[j].reshape(10), align = "center")
    plt.xticks(np.arange(10),np.arange(10).astype(str))
    j += 1
    count += 1

    plt.subplot(45, 4, count)
    plt.title("Example of Digit: "+ str(Y_test[listX[j]]))
    plt.imshow(X_test[listX[j]].reshape(28,28), cmap = "gray")
    plt.axis("off")
    count += 1

    probs = model.predict_proba(X_test_digit, batch_size = 1)
    plt.subplot(45, 4, count)
    plt.title("Probabilities for Each Digit Class")
    plt.bar(np.arange(10), listY[j].reshape(10), align = "center")
    plt.xticks(np.arange(10),np.arange(10).astype(str))
    j += 1
    count += 1
    plt.show()
